OL,5,Cstabber
OL,7,FDuring the trial, the court heard how
OL,8,Fthe schoolgirl had followed Ms Elias
OL,9,Finto the yard after being asked to
OL,10,Fleave a school hall. It was there she
OL,11,Flaunched her attack, stabbing Ms Elias
OL,12,Fand Ms Hopkin while shouting "I want
OL,13,Fto kill you".
OL,15,FThe jury heard the girl brought a
OL,16,Fknife to school every day. Officers
OL,17,Falso found a notebook belonging to the
OL,18,Fpupil which contained cruel drawings
OL,19,Fof Ms Elias and an admission that she
OL,20,Fwanted to commit the "crime of a
OL,21,Flifetime".
