OL,7,FFollowing the teenage girl's guilty
OL,8,Fverdict, Fiona Elias said: "This
OL,9,Fverdict should be seen as a clear
OL,10,Fmessage for pupils across the country.
OL,11,FI would not want any individual to go
OL,12,Fthrough the nightmare I have endured
OL,13,Fduring the last nine months."
OL,15,FWith the girl due to be sentenced
OL,16,Ftoday at Swansea Crown Court, Mr
OL,17,FCampbell says he's keen for justice to
OL,18,Fbe served, with instances of violence
OL,19,Ftowards teachers in schools on the
OL,20,Frise.
